Structured Query Language (SQL) databases are the go to solution for most small projects and products. They provide a high performance way to query relational data across many different axis.
However, SQL databases have problems scaling which is why most companies eventually find themselves moving off SQL solutions and onto NoSQL alternatives. So why don't SQL databases scale? SQL databases rely on structured data and foreign keys to connect data. This is an extremely performant way to manage data and lets you link data across the whole database with simple queries using SELECT and JOIN. SELECT Customers.CustomerName, Orders.OrderID FROM Customers LEFT JOIN Orders ON Customers.CustomerID=Orders.CustomerID ORDER BY Customers.CustomerName;
